{"title": "Short Nonfiction Collection, Vol. 048", "description": "Fifteen short nonfiction works in the public domain, independently chosen by the readers. Topics include philosophy and thought--Phtah-Hotep, Petrarch, Diderot, Bertrand Russell, and the Weymouth New Testament; adventure and travel--a survival story by Mark Twain and a woman's sojourn in Saltillo, Mexico; immigration and war--Benjamin Franklin on the assimilation of German speakers, Lincoln's Gettysburg Address, the League of Nations, and an essay on potatoes and war; geology--on the origins of chalk; a critique of one-act plays, a biography of H.H. Munro (Saki), and Emerson's advice to Thoreau to clear his brain by writing poetry.\n<br><br>\nAphorisms by Diderot was translated by <a href=\"https://librivox.org/author/12714\">Margaret Jourdain</a>\nPetrarch's Secret was translated by <a href=\"https://librivox.org/author/12715\">William H. Draper</a>\nThe Instruction of Ptah-Hotep was translated by <a href=\"https://librivox.org/author/12664\">Battiscombe G. Gunn</a>", "duration": 19977, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "18", "name": " Various"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/nonfiction048_1705_librivox/snf048_1705.jpg", "copyright_year": "0", "genres": ["*Non-fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Sue Anderson"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Craig Campbell"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Aphorisms 15-22 (1746)", "readers": [3374], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/nonfiction048_1705_librivox/snf048_aphorisms_diderot_cc_64kb.mp3", "duration": 960}, {"section": 2, "title": "Emerson and Thoreau, November 10, 1838", "readers": [3003], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/nonfiction048_1705_librivox/snf048_emersonjournal_emerson_sa_64kb.mp3", "duration": 264}, {"section": 3, "title": "Forty-Three Days in an Open Boat", "r